From: H618 video enablement <noreply@local>
Subject: [PATCH] drm/sun4i: vi_layer: re-enable NV12/YUV on DE33 VI plane

patches.drm limits the DE33 VI layer to RGB (chroma upscaling unsupported).
For direct-to-plane video at native resolution the scaler is bypassed and
DE33 channel CSC is implemented, so re-advertise the common HW-decoder
output formats for zero-copy Cedrus NV12 scanout. Rebased onto the current
patches.drm DE33 format array.
---
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/sun4i/sun8i_vi_layer.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/sun4i/sun8i_vi_layer.c
@@ -432,6 +432,12 @@
 	DRM_FORMAT_RGBX8888,
 	DRM_FORMAT_XBGR8888,
 	DRM_FORMAT_XRGB8888,
+	DRM_FORMAT_NV12,
+	DRM_FORMAT_NV21,
+	DRM_FORMAT_YUV420,
+	DRM_FORMAT_YVU420,
+	DRM_FORMAT_YUYV,
+	DRM_FORMAT_UYVY,
 };
 
 static const uint64_t sun8i_layer_modifiers[] = {
